  <prompt>Migrate Document Intelligence + other AI service direct `IDistributedCache.` calls to `ITenantCache`. Specifically: `EmbeddingCache`, `GraphTokenCache`, `GraphMetadataCache`, any `Services/Ai/*` consumer outside Chat/Membership (covered already). Preserve `SemaphoreSlim` rate-limit patterns (ADR-013).</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke .NET developer with AI service rate-limit familiarity.</role>
  <goal>`grep -rn "IDistributedCache\." src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/` (excluding Chat + Membership directories which are already migrated) returns ZERO unflagged matches.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Existing wrappers (`EmbeddingCache`, `GraphTokenCache`, `GraphMetadataCache`, `CachedAccessDataSource`) use `IDistributedCache` INTERNALLY. Their public API stays — internal calls migrate to `ITenantCache`. Per spec Assumption: if a wrapper's public API needs to change to expose tenantId, escalate.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
